race.comment: Sticking with the progressive STEALTH OF NIGHT (5) who has won her past two. They haven't been dominant wins but she's put herself on speed and won well enough as a short priced favourite each time. This is only her 7th career start and she profiles as if she'll continue to raise the bar. HOT DIGITY BOOM (13) ran well first up at Sandown Lakeside over 1200m, getting home late for fourth. 1400m suits now and his best 3yo form would take some beating here. LEGACY BAY (14) has placed in all three runs back from a spell, getting home late again to just miss at Sandown Lakeside last start. She gets in light here and will be winding up out wide. PORTER (4) will be up on speed and is racing well. 1400m is his best trip. FEAR NO EVIL (3) is going okay in NSW and should give a sight.
